  "notes": "Skeleton. Old Irish (c. 600-900). The pervasive broad/slender (velarised vs palatalised) consonant contrast is conditioned by the flanking vowels and is NOT encoded here, so the engine outputs the broad/default reflex only and a high PER is expected. Lenited spellings th/ch/ph and nasal clusters mb/nd/ng mapped to their fricative/prenasalised reflexes.",
